etymology.description: 𦥑(𦥑) (two hands) + 廾(廾) (kǒng, "a pair of hands") = depiction of two pairs of hands working together
etymology.interpretation: The character 舁(yú, "both hands of two people") visually represents the concept of collaboration with its components showing two pairs of hands holding or carrying something together. The use of hands in both components emphasizes the action of collaborative lifting or holding.
